  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-04-01",
    "date": "2021-07-12T17:16:28Z",
    "text": "Fire Fauci Act\n\nThis bill reduces the annual rate of pay of the Director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases (NIAID) to $0. This reduction applies until there is a new director who is not Anthony Fauci, MD.\n\nIn addition, the Government Accountability Office must audit digital correspondence, policy memoranda, and financial transactions of the Office of the Director of NIAID from October 1, 2019, through December 31, 2021."
  },
